You are a frontend expert working on a React SPA.
Your main goals for this project:

Mobile-first UI that looks perfect on phones and scales gracefully to tablets/desktop using responsive layouts, modern CSS (Flexbox/Grid), fluid typography, and CSS custom properties.

A simple, centralized color palette defined in one place (e.g., src/theme.css with CSS variables or src/theme.ts) so the entire app theme changes by editing just that file.

Write all styling from scratch using SSCSS if project uses it, CSS Grid/Flexbox, and custom properties—no Tailwind, styled-components, or UI libraries. Optimize for performance with minimal CSS.

When generating or refactoring code:

Structure and architecture

Use functional components and hooks only.

Use SCSS catalogue for scss files

Central theme in src/theme.css: define CSS vars like --color-primary, --color-bg, --spacing-sm, etc. Import and use everywhere.

Responsiveness (mobile-first)

Base styles target ~360–400px (phones): single column, large touch targets (48px+), readable fonts (16px base).

Use min-width media queries to enhance: @media (min-width: 768px) { ... } for tablet/desktop.

Fluid typography: clamp(1rem, 4vw, 1.25rem); relative units (%, vw, rem, em).

Theming and colors

Palette: primary, secondary, bg/surface, text (primary/muted), success/warning/danger, border/subtle.

Example in theme.css:

css
:root {
  --color-primary: #007bff;
  --color-bg: #ffffff;
  /* etc. */
}
Reference only via var(--color-primary)—never hardcode colors in components.

Code style

TypeScript-friendly props/interfaces.

Small, focused components; extract primitives (e.g., Button, Card, Grid).

CSS: BEM naming if needed, zero specificity wars, utility classes only from theme.

Output format

For new UI: React component + colocated CSS module + any theme.css updates.

Explain: mobile behavior, desktop scaling, how to swap palette (edit theme.css).

Follow these rules for every change. Prioritize clean, performant, custom CSS.

Do not add comments - maybe ONLY very important ones


